<TITLE> Mashrafee, Ashraful win BSWA best sportsman awards </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 15 (bdnews24.com) - Cricketers Mashrafee Bin Mortaza and Mohammad Ashraful have been selected as the best sportsmen for 2006 and 2005 respectively by the Bangladesh Sports Writers Association (BSWA) Wednesday. National cricket team captain Ashraful and vice captain Mashrafee will receive the SA Mohsin Trophies, introduced by the BSWA, which also announced the names of the best players in different disciplines . The announcement also covered the names of the best referee, umpire, patron and the active organisation for the years of 2005 and 2006. Nominees for the award of 2006 are: Arif Khan Joy (football), Shahriar Nafees (cricket), Rasel Khan Bappi (hockey), Shahjahan Ali Ronny (swimming), Mizanur Rahman (taekwondo), Siddiqur Rahman (golf), Reefat Bin Sattar (chess), Jahid Hasan Amily (promising talent, football), Laboni Akhter Jui (sportswomen, swimming), Nadir Shah (umpire, cricket), Kutubuddin Ahmed (organiser), Ispahani Limited (patron), Kazi Alamgir (special contribution for sports) and Mashrafee Bin Mortaza (sportsman of the year 2006). Nominees for the award of 2005 are: Mohammad Sujan (football), Javed Omar (cricket), Russel Mahmud Jimy (hockey), Enamul Haq Jr (promising talent, cricket), Mollah Sabira Sultana (sportswomen, weightlifting), Taieb Hasan Shamsuddin Babu (football referee), Nurul Alam Chowdhury (organiser), Sirajul Islam Bachchu (special contribution for sports), Mousumi Industries Limited (patron), Narayanganj DSA (active organisation) and Mohammad Ashraful (sportsman of the year 2005). 
